This paper discusses the design of a secure middlebox framework for deploying high-performance Network Functions (NFs) on untrusted commodity servers. The paper focuses on security and network processing, which suggests that the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
